import pandas as pd
  
# intialise data of lists.
data = {'Category':['Breakfast', 'Beef & Pork', 'Chicken & Fish', 'Salads',
       'Snacks & Sides', 'Desserts', 'Beverages', 'Coffee & Tea',
       'Smoothies & Shakes'],
        'Variety':[42,15,27,6,13,7,27,95,28]}
  
# Create DataFrame
df2= pd.DataFrame(data)
  
# Print the output.

As seen above I created a list of the unique values of category and via for loop we obtained the number of items in each category and then made a graphical representation of all the varieties. From the above visualizations, it can be inferred that Coffee & Tea have the highest number of varieties with 95 and salads has the least with 6. In terms of percentage ,Coffee comprises of 36.54 % of the number of Varieties and salads with 2.31%
